      "topic": "architecture",
      "content": "Use a tiny Node.js server (~80 lines, zero dependencies) with Server-Sent Events (SSE) to push compilation updates to the browser in real time. SSE beats WebSockets here: one-way data flow, auto-reconnect built into the browser, and zero npm dependencies.",
